# Cloudflare Pages _headers (application layer). Additive to zone-level hardening.
#
# Scope note: this file carries APP headers only. HSTS is intentionally absent here:
# it is set at the Cloudflare zone level, and duplicating it risks conflicting max-age.
#
# Content-Security-Policy is ENFORCED (as of 2026-07-06). It shipped Report-Only for one
# staging round, was verified clean across Chromium 148, Firefox 152, WebKit 26.5, and real
# Safari hardware, then flipped to enforced after the Cloudflare Web Analytics beacon was
# removed (the site now loads zero external scripts, so script-src 'self' is honest and
# enforcement blocks nothing). There is NO reporting endpoint (report-to / report-uri) by
# design; violations surface in browser devtools.
#
# script-src note (important): the production build emits 18 distinct inline scripts, not
# one. Besides our reading-progress bar, Starlight injects its own inline scripts (theme
# provider, mobile-menu toggle, sidebar/TOC persistence, updatePickers, Expressive Code),
# and the marketing pages (/ and /about) plus a few writeups carry their own inline FX.
# A hash in script-src makes browsers ignore 'unsafe-inline', so a single progress-script
# hash would block the other 17. We therefore keep 'unsafe-inline' in script-src.
# The stable progress-script hash is sha256-zbeMm3179IyQub695L7lMzB1ygPiSe0lSSrMfkEOwpc=
# (recompute the full set from dist to drop unsafe-inline later; see DECISIONS.md).
#
# 'wasm-unsafe-eval' is REQUIRED, not optional: Starlight's search (Pagefind) instantiates a
# WebAssembly module inside a Web Worker (dist/pagefind/pagefind-worker.js + wasm.*.pagefind).
# Under CSP, WASM compilation needs 'wasm-unsafe-eval' (or the broader 'unsafe-eval'); without
# it the browser blocks it (blockedURI "wasm-eval", CompileError under enforcement) and search
# breaks. Verified across Chromium 148, Firefox 152, and WebKit 26.5: WASM runs clean with the
# token, blocked without it. 'wasm-unsafe-eval' is the narrow WASM-only token (does NOT permit
# JS eval / new Function), a minimal targeted relaxation. NOTE: worker-context CSP violations
# do NOT surface on the main-thread securitypolicyviolation listener or console, so a search
# smoke test can look clean while WASM is actually being flagged; probe WASM directly.
#
# style-src keeps 'unsafe-inline': Starlight and Expressive Code inject inline styles.
# That is effectively permanent short of forking Starlight.
#
# Do NOT add Trusted Types (require-trusted-types-for / trusted-types). The SecretTerminal
# (src/components/SecretTerminal.astro) renders via innerHTML; visitor input is escaped and
# only trusted authored markup is injected raw, so it is safe, but Trusted Types blocks
# innerHTML sinks and would break it. Standard CSP is fully compatible.
#
# frame-ancestors 'none' and upgrade-insecure-requests were inert under Report-Only and are
# now ACTIVE under enforcement: frame-ancestors adds clickjacking defense alongside the
# enforced X-Frame-Options: DENY above, and upgrade-insecure-requests upgrades any same-origin
# subresource request to HTTPS.
#
# Permissions-Policy denies powerful features the site does not use (fullscreen too: the
# image-zoom overlay is a CSS transform, not the Fullscreen API). Pruned 2026-07-06 of six
# tokens that current Chromium/Edge no longer recognize and log as "Unrecognized feature"
# (ambient-light-sensor, battery, document-domain, execution-while-not-rendered,
# execution-while-out-of-viewport, speaker-selection). Header values cannot be multiline, so
# the policy is one line.
#
# Cross-browser verified: zero violations under this policy on Chromium 148, Firefox 152,
# WebKit 26.5 (Safari engine, via Playwright), and real Safari hardware (iPhone, iPad, and
# macOS Safari): synthetic main+worker WASM, the real Pagefind search, and every real page,
# both themes.

/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), autoplay=(), camera=(), display-capture=(), encrypted-media=(), fullscreen=(), gamepad=(), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), hid=(), idle-detection=(), local-fonts=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), midi=(), payment=(), picture-in-picture=(), publickey-credentials-get=(), screen-wake-lock=(), serial=(), usb=(), web-share=(), xr-spatial-tracking=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'wasm-unsafe-eval'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; font-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'self'; upgrade-insecure-requests

# Hashed, content-addressed build assets: safe to cache hard and forever.
/_astro/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

# Self-hosted subset WOFF2 fonts: content-stable filenames, cache hard and forever.
# CAVEAT: immutable means a year with NO revalidation. These filenames are NOT content-hashed,
# so if a font is ever re-subset or replaced you MUST change its filename (or bump a ?v= query),
# otherwise returning visitors keep the stale cached file for up to a year. Record any such
# change in DECISIONS.md / CORE_SPEC.md.
/fonts/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
